						               													<description>Oganika is a puzzle- and strategy game that is easy to learn but will challenge the smartest of minds! Oganika can be played in three game modes: a puzzle (single player), as a battle (puzzle against an opponent) and as a multiplayer strategy game with a board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Playing Oganika is simple: place any of the 36 tiles into a given arrangement, making sure that all the lines on the surface designs of the tiles match at connection points. Each set of tiles contains two different types, left handed and right handed. Some game modes only use one type, others use a mixture of both.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In multiplayer mode, the goal of each round is to add as many pieces as possible to a single 36-tile hexagon. The game is played with two sets of tiles (included in the game) and players take turns to add tiles to the single hexagon in the middle of the table. Plays like blocking players, choosing the right number of new tiles or reducing your play time to pressure other players make this game fast, fun but most of all strategic.  The person who lays the most tiles, wins the round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
